15 PART 2
16 PROVISIONS CONCERNING APPROPRIATIONS
17 FOR FISCAL YEAR ENDING SEPTEMBER 30, 2025
18 GENERAL SECTIONS
19 Sec. 201. In accordance with section 30 of article IX of the
20 state constitution of 1963, for the fiscal year ending September
21 30, 2025, total state spending under part 1 from state sources is
22 $41,766,000 and state spending under part 1 from state sources to
23 be paid to local units of government is $26,326,000. The following
24 itemized statement identifies appropriations from which spending to
25 local units of government will occur:
26 Acquisition grants-in-aid $ 7,412,600.00
27 Development grants-in-aid 18,913,400.00
28 Total payments to locals $ 26,326,000.00
29 Sec. 202. The appropriations under this part and part 1 are
TMV H01040'25 (H-1) f07zim

11
1 subject to the management and budget act, 1984 PA 431, MCL 18.1101
2 to 18.1594.
3 Sec. 203. Funds appropriated in part 1 must not be expended
4 for utility scale solar or wind development projects.
5
6 MICHIGAN NATURAL RESOURCES TRUST FUND
7 Sec. 301. (1) The department of natural resources shall enter
8 into agreements with local units of government to administer the
9 grants identified in part 1. Among other provisions, the agreements
10 must require that grant recipients do all of the following:
11 (a) Dedicate to public outdoor recreation uses in perpetuity
12 the land acquired or developed.
13 (b) Replace lands converted or lost to other than public
14 outdoor recreation use.
15 (c) For parcels acquired that are larger than 5 acres, provide
16 this state with a nonparticipating 1/6 minimum royalty interest in
17 any acquired minerals that are retained by the grant recipient.
18 (2) The agreements under subsection (1) must also provide that
19 the full payments of grants be made only after proof of
20 acquisition, or proof of completion of a development project, is
21 submitted by the grant recipient and all costs are verified by the
22 department of natural resources. This requirement may be waived by
23 the department of natural resources.
24 Sec. 302. The appropriations in part 1 for capital outlay
25 shall be carried forward at the end of the fiscal year consistent
26 with section 248 of the management and budget act, 1984 PA 431, MCL
27 18.1248.
28 Sec. 303. (1) The state share of the capital outlay
29 appropriations authorized in 2022 PA 151 for the following Michigan
